---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words Ending in -LESS — FECKLESS, RECKLESS, HELPLESS" description="Master -LESS suffix bingos: FECKLESS (17pts), RECKLESS (14pts), HELPLESS (13pts). Negation adjective patterns for 50-point bonus plays." keywords="scrabble words ending in less, feckless scrabble, reckless scrabble, helpless scrabble, less suffix bingo, negation adjectives scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Ending in -LESS — FECKLESS, RECKLESS, HELPLESS","description":"Master -LESS suffix bingos: FECKLESS (17pts), RECKLESS (14pts), HELPLESS (13pts). Negation adjective patterns.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-less"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best -LESS words for Scrabble bingos?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"FECKLESS leads at 17 points (8 letters) with the K worth 5 and C worth 3. RECKLESS scores 14 points, and HELPLESS scores 13. All are 8-letter bingo plays earning the 50-point bonus."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why is -LESS good for bingos?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"-LESS is 4 tiles (L+E+S+S) that attach to many roots to form 8-letter words. Since most -LESS words are exactly 8 letters, they use all 7 rack tiles plus one board letter — perfect bingo length."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What roots work with -LESS for high scores?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"High-value roots include FECK (K=5pts), RECK (K+C=8pts), HELP (H+P=7pts), RUTH (rare root, 7pts), and HOPE (H+P=7pts). Look for roots containing K, H, P, or F for maximum base scores."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in -LESS — Negation Adjective Bingos</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The -LESS suffix is a bingo machine. It turns any short root into an 8-letter negation adjective — FECKLESS, RECKLESS, HELPLESS. With L, E, S, S on your rack, you only need 4 more tiles to hit that 50-point bonus. FECKLESS leads at 17 points base before premium squares, and the double-S means you're using two of the most common tiles in the bag.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (FECKLESS)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letters (Bingo Length)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Suffix Tiles (LESS)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">50+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bonus Points</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top -LESS Words for Bingos</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 FECKLESS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">17 pts · 8 letters · F(4)+E(1)+C(3)+K(5)+L(1)+E(1)+S(1)+S(1)</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 RECKLESS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · 8 letters · R(1)+E(1)+C(3)+K(5)+L(1)+E(1)+S(1)+S(1)</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ HELPLESS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · 8 letters · H(4)+E(1)+L(1)+P(3)+L(1)+E(1)+S(1)+S(1)</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ HOPELESS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · 8 letters · H(4)+O(1)+P(3)+E(1)+L(1)+E(1)+S(1)+S(1)</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">-LESS Bingo Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold L+E+S+S:</span> When you see these four tiles on your rack, start thinking -LESS. You need exactly 4 root tiles (or 3 + a board letter) for an 8-letter bingo. The double-S is your signal.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target K and F roots:</span> K(5pts) and F(4pts) roots give -LESS words their highest base scores. FECKLESS and RECKLESS both use K. RUTHLESS uses H(4). These consonant-heavy roots are the premium plays.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">8 letters = perfect bingo:</span> Most -LESS words are exactly 8 letters — that's 7 from your rack plus one tile already on the board. Look for an open E, R, or S to extend through.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FECKLESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RECKLESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HELPLESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HOPELESS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">-LESS creates <span class="text-white font-medium">negation adjectives</span> from almost any noun or verb root. Unlike -FUL (which affirms), -LESS denies — meaning for every -FUL word your opponent knows, there's often a -LESS counterpart they haven't considered.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ful/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -FUL</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ness/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -NESS</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/common-bingo-endings/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Common Bingo Endings</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find -LESS bingos from your rack — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
